                <h1>Understanding Virginia's 7-Year Background Check Law</h1>
                <p>In Virginia, a 7-year background check law limits what employers can consider during hiring. This law mandates that employers can only look back 7 years for felony convictions, promoting fair employment practices. However, some offenses, like serious crimes, can still be disclosed beyond this timeframe, ensuring safety and compliance.</p>
